                            <comment id="13945853" author="alangates" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2014 23:18:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rhbutani&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rhbutani&quot;&gt;rhbutani&lt;/a&gt; This needs to be in 0.13 as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13948884" author="alangates" created="Thu, 27 Mar 2014 04:44:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ran tests locally, all looks good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13949636" author="ashutoshc" created="Thu, 27 Mar 2014 17:20:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gates&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gates&quot;&gt;gates&lt;/a&gt; Can you create RB entry for it ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13949658" author="alangates" created="Thu, 27 Mar 2014 17:31:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I changed the grain of locking for DDL statements.  In the initial checkin I had set all DDL statements to exclusive lock.  But this results in a whole table being locked so that a partition can be added.  This is excessive.  So I went back and added a DDL_EXCLUSIVE, DDL_SHARED, and DDL_NO_LOCK so that different DDL statements could obtain appropriate grains of locks.  For example, add partition is now a shared lock, drop partition is an exclusive lock, and add function is no lock.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13949659" author="alangates" created="Thu, 27 Mar 2014 17:31:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created review board &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/19736/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/19736/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
